replies.msg: Can a strategic plan truly yield bottom-line results? Or is it just a waste of time?
The answer to both questions can be yes. It's critical to plan for success. More importantly, there are steps to follow to make it happen.

Most businesses don't do any strategic planning. And, of the ones who do, most treat it as nothing more than an academic exercise. This is unfortunate. With some effort and a willingness to make hard decisions, it's possible to create more than just strategy.

我遇見誰 會有怎樣的對白
我等的人 他在多遠的未來
It's possible to realize bottom-line results from a well-developed strategic plan that is then put into action and followed through.
Get it while it's hot, not when it's cool
You just got the news no one wants to hear. Shari is leaving. The one person the organization can't function without. This is an absolute nightmare. What do you do now?
People in business always come and go. You should do these three key things to make sure your business can continue to function through any transition.

慢慢喜歡你
慢慢的親密
慢慢聊自己
慢慢和你走在一起
假如你有親友已經工作一段日子，但仍時刻尋找進修機會，希望將來有更好的發展，請你告訴他們，理大香港專上學院 (PolyU HKCC) 新設立「重返校園獎學金」，鼓勵這些之前因為種種原因而暫時放棄學業的同學重拾書本，入讀HKCC考取副學位資歷，然後再向學士學位課程邁進，實現未完的夢想。
